<p>After continuing down the corridor for some time, the faceless man came to a stop in front of a door. The number on the doorplate was 208. <q>It isn't locked. You should be the one to open it.</q> I did as I was told and opened the door. Beyond it lay a large room. It seemed to be part of a suite of rooms in an old-fashioned hotel. The ceiling was high, and from it hung an old-fashioned chandelier. The chandelier was not lit. A small wall lamp gave off a gloomy light, the only source of illumination in the room. The curtains were closed tight.</p>

