<p>A sound from the kitchen woke me up. When I went to investigate, Creta Kano was there, making breakfast, wearing a white T-shirt and blue shorts, both of which belonged to Kumiko.</p>

<p><q>Where are your clothes?</q> I demanded, standing in the kitchen door.</p>

<p><q>Oh, I'm sorry. You were asleep, so I took the liberty of borrowing some of your wife's clothing. I knew it was terribly forward of me, but I didn't have a thing to wear,</q> said Creta Kano, turning just her head to look at me. At some point since I last saw her, she had reverted to her usual sixties style of hair and makeup, lacking only the fake eyelashes.</p>

<p><q>No, that's no problem,</q> I said. <q>What I want to know is what happened to your clothes.</q></p>

<p><q>I lost them,</q> she said simply.</p>

<p><q>Lost them?</q></p>

<p><q>Yes. I lost them somewhere.</q></p>

<p>I stepped into the kitchen and watched, leaning against the table, as Creta Kano made an omelette. With deft movements, she cracked the eggs, added seasoning, and beat the mixture. <q>Meaning you came here naked?</q></p>

